    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Glyphs carved on wooden tablets or board found on Easter Island and believed to be part of a boustrophedon writing system utilized as ceremonial mnemonic devices. All deciphering attempts of the rongo-rongo have failed. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046814/Lee, Rock Art of Easter Island (1992)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000045262/Grove Dictionary of Art online (1999-2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Glifos tallados en tabletas o tablas de madera encontradas en Isla de Pascua y se cree que son parte de un sistema de escritura bustrofedona utilizada en elementos ceremoniales mnemónicos. Todos los intentos de descifrar los rongo-rongo han fracasado. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Reliëffiguren die zijn gesneden uit houten tabletten of platen, te vinden op Paaseiland en waarschijnlijk een onderdeel van een boustrofedon-schriftsysteem dat werd gebruikt voor ceremoniële geheugensteuntjes. Het is nog niet gelukt om het rongorongo te ontcijferen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>見於復活島的木板雕刻，普遍認為文字是以犂耕式轉行書寫法刻寫而成，於儀式祭典上用來記錄以助記憶，至今尚無法成功解開瞭解其中涵義。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Glifos esculpidos em tábuas de madeiras encontradas na Easter Island (Ilha de Páscoa) e que acredita-se que são parte de um sistema de escrita bustrofédon utilizado como dispositivo mnemônico cerimonial. Todas as tentativas para decifrar rongo-rongo falharam.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
